<% layout("/layout/boilerplate") -%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/5.14.0/css/all.min.css"
      integrity="sha512-1PKOgIY59xJ8Co8+NE6FZ+LOAZKjy+KY8iq0G4B3CyeY6wYHN3yt9PW0XpSriVlkMXe40PTKnXrLnZ9+fkDaog=="
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/Faq.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/home.css" />
    <title>Know Before You Go | Mystic Odisha FAQ</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1 class="faqh">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

    <div class="faq-container">
      <div class="faq-card ">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <h3 class="faq-title dark-mood-text">What is the best time to visit Odisha?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle">
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
          </span>
        </div>
        <p class="faq-text dark-mood-text">
          The best time to visit Odisha is from October to March when the
          weather is pleasant and ideal for sightseeing. The monsoon season
          (June to September) brings lush greenery, while summers (April to
          June) can be hot.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-card">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <h3 class="faq-title dark-mood-text">What is the significance of the Jagannath Temple in Puri?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle">
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
          </span>
        </div>
        <p class="faq-text dark-mood-text">
          The Jagannath Temple is one of the Char Dham pilgrimage sites in
          Hinduism. It is famous for the Rath Yatra (Chariot Festival), where
          Lord Jagannath, Balabhadra, and Subhadra are taken in grand chariots
          through the city.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-card">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <h3 class="faq-title dark-mood-text">Is Odisha safe for tourists?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle">
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
          </span>
        </div>
        <p class="faq-text dark-mood-text">
          Yes, Odisha is safe for tourists. However, visitors should take basic
          precautions like avoiding isolated areas at night and keeping
          valuables secure.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-card">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <h3 class="faq-title dark-mood-text">How can I reach Odisha?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle">
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
          </span>
        </div>
        <p class="faq-text dark-mood-text">
          By Air: The main airport is Biju Patnaik International Airport
          (Bhubaneswar), well-connected to major cities.<br /><br />
          By Train: Odisha has a good rail network with major stations like
          Bhubaneswar, Puri, and Cuttack.<br /><br />
          By Road: Well-connected highways make road travel convenient from
          neighboring states.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-card">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <h3 class="faq-title dark-mood-text">Is online booking available for Odisha Tourism hotels and packages?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle">
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
          </span>
        </div>
        <p class="faq-text dark-mood-text">
          Yes, you can book hotels and tour packages through the official Odisha
          Tourism website and other travel portals.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-card">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <h3 class="faq-title dark-mood-text">What are the must-try foods in Odisha?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle">
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
          </span>
        </div>
        <p class="faq-text dark-mood-text">
          Dalma (Lentils & Vegetables)<br /><br />
          Chhena Poda (Sweet Dish)<br /><br />
          Pakhala Bhata (Fermented Rice)<br /><br />
          Mahaprasad of Jagannath Temple
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-card">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <h3 class="faq-title dark-mood-text">Which wildlife sanctuaries can I visit in Odisha?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle">
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
          </span>
        </div>
        <p class="faq-text dark-mood-text">
          Bhitarkanika National Park (Crocodiles & Mangroves)<br /><br />
          Simlipal Tiger Reserve<br /><br />
          Chilika Lake (Bird Sanctuary & Dolphins)
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-card">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <h3 class="faq-title dark-mood-text">Are there any adventure sports available in Odisha?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle">
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
          </span>
        </div>
        <p class="faq-text dark-mood-text">
          Yes! You can enjoy boating, trekking (Mahendragiri Hills),
          parasailing, and water sports in Gopalpur & Chandrabhaga beaches.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-card">
        <div class="faq-header">
          <h3 class="faq-title dark-mood-text">What are the best travel packages available for Odisha?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle">
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
            <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
          </span>
        </div>
        <p class="faq-text dark-mood-text">
          Golden Triangle Tour (Bhubaneswar, Puri, Konark)<br /><br />
          Eco-Tourism & Wildlife Package (Chilika, Simlipal, Bhitarkanika)<br /><br />
          Tribal Tourism Tour
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <script src="/js/Faq.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>